        "text": "18",
        "rationale": "Subtracting the lengths is not the Pythagorean theorem."
      },
      {
        "id": "B",
        "text": "30",
        "rationale": "Correct."
      },
      {
        "id": "C",
        "text": "50",
        "rationale": "Add/subtract under the square root, not outside it."
      },
      {
        "id": "D",
        "text": "31",
        "rationale": "Off by one; recompute c² − a²."
      }
    ],
    "correct_choice": "B",
    "explanation": "By the Pythagorean theorem, leg = √(c² − a²) = √(1156 − 256) = √900 = 30.",
    "estimated_time_seconds": 85,
